ScrollView

A scroll view is a mechanism to handle smaller screens which enables scrolling when the content exceeds the screen size. It can only contain one view group, but that does not include nested view groups.

Example:

<LinearLayout
    xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:orientation="vertical">

    <ScrollView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:fillViewport="true"
        android:isScrollContainer="true">

        // Nested views and view groups

    </ScrollView>

</LinearLayout>
